definition.value: One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Vardar, located in the central part of Macedonia, borders Greece to the south. Internally, it borders Pelagonia, Southwestern, Skopje, Southeastern, and Eastern.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Southeastern, located in the southeastern part of the country, borders Greece and Bulgaria. Internally, it borders Vardar and Eastern statistical regions.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Pelagonia statistical region is located in southwestern part of the Republic of Macedonia. It borders Greece and Albania. Internally, it borders Southwestern and Vardar statistical regions.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Polog, located in the northwestern part of the country, borders Albania and Kosovo. Internally, it borders Southwestern and Skopje statistical regions.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Skopje, located in northern Macedonia, borders Serbia to the north. Internally, it borders Vardar, Polog, Northeastern, Eastern, and Southwestern statistical regions.

A district in Moldova. Holercani, Marcauti, Molovata, Oxentea, and Ustia are situated on the western (right) bank of the river Dniester, while the other 10 - on the eastern bank, of which six (Cocieri, Vasilievca, Corjova, Mahala, Molovata Noua, and Roghi) - north of the city of Dubasari, itself under the control of the separatist authorities of Transnistria, and the remaining four -south of the city. The village of Vasilievca, as well as considerable parts of the farmland of the villages of Cocieri, Roghi, and Dorotcaia are situated east of the Tiraspol-Dubasari-Rabnita road.
